.TH JFETCH 1 "2026" "The-JLC-Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
jfetch \- display system information with ASCII art
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B jfetch
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B jfetch
displays system information in a formatted output alongside ASCII art.
It retrieves and displays the following information:
.TP
.B Username and Hostname
Current user and system hostname.
.TP
.B OS and Kernel
Operating system name and kernel version.
.TP
.B Uptime
System uptime in days, hours, and minutes.
.TP
.B RAM
Free and total memory usage.
.TP
.B Disk
Used and total disk space in human-readable format.
.TP
.B Shell
Current shell path.
.TP
.B Terminal
Terminal type (TERM environment variable).
.TP
.B Window Manager
Detected window manager (checks for dwm).
.TP
.B Architecture
CPU architecture.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful execution.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Display system information:
.EX
jfetch
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR fetch (1),
.BR uname (1),
.BR free (1)
.SH AUTHORS
The-JLC-Project contributors.
